# 🏭 Pollution Analysis Project

This project is focused on analyzing air pollution data and its relationship with public health.

## 📊 Project Features

- Cleaning and preprocessing pollution data
- Handling missing values and outliers
- Converting dates to datetime format
- Monthly analysis of PM2.5 levels
- Correlation analysis with health indicators (number of patients, etc.)
- Data visualizations using seaborn and matplotlib:
  - 📈 Line plot: Pollution trends over time
  - 📉 Scatter plot: Pollution vs. number of patients
  - 📊 Histogram: Monthly pollution levels


## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python (pandas, matplotlib, seaborn)
- Jupyter Notebook
- Git & GitHub

